# Pytest Standards

## Test Types
- Unit tests: isolate pure functions/services with fast feedback
- Integration tests: test Flask routes with test client and realistic wiring
- Contract tests: verify request/response shape against OpenAPI where possible

## Naming and Layout
- File names: `test_<feature>.py`
- Test names: `test_<behavior>_<expected_result>`
- Group tests by domain module, not by technical layer only

## Fixtures
- Use fixtures for setup reuse, keep scope minimal (`function` by default)
- Prefer factory fixtures/builders to inline payload duplication
- Avoid hidden mutable global state across tests

## Assertions
- One primary behavior per test
- Assert both status code and response payload contract for API tests
- For failure paths, assert stable error code/message keys

## Execution
- Default: `pytest -q`
- Coverage: `pytest --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing`
